  "body": "We only update `previous_epoch_randao_mix` if validator registry update happens.\r\nIn the meantime, `state.slot` gets incremented every incoming block. Will we run into an issue in `get_crosslink_committees_at_slot` under condition `slot < state_epoch_slot` for `get_previous_epoch_committee_count_per_slot` where  `state.previous_epoch_randao_mix` does not correlate to previous epoch's randao mix because it falls behind? \r\n\r\nShould [validator registry](https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/master/specs/core/0_beacon-chain.md#validator-registry) start out with:\r\n```\r\nFirst, update previous_epoch_calculation_slot and previous_epoch_start_shard:\r\n\r\nSet state.previous_epoch_calculation_slot = state.current_epoch_calculation_slot\r\nSet state.previous_epoch_start_shard = state.current_epoch_start_shard\r\nSet state.previous_epoch_randao_mix = state.current_epoch_randao_mix\r\n```",
